[h2 
	" Kirby And The Amazing Mirror Any% TAS
	$LF
]h2
[p 
	"Note: English is not my first language.
	$LF
]p
[h3 
	" About the game
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	[q 
		"Kirby And The Amazing Mirror is the second Kirby game released on GBA and is one of the most unique and different 
		$LF
		"Kirby games so far. The story involves some sort of parallel universe in which some evil force has gained entrance 
		$LF
		"to the normal universe and things are just all over flip flopped.
	]q
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"The game is like Kirby - Nightmare In Dreamland (the Remake of NES Kirby's Adventure). 
	$LF
	"It uses the same sprites and same midbosses etc.. However, you are able to choose your own path and many abilities were upgraded.
	$LF
	"And there are other Kirbys controlled by the game that you can call if you're in trouble (not used in the run).
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"The game's goal is to collect 8 mirror pieces in order to enter the big mirror in the main hall where the endbosses are waiting for you.
	$LF
]p
[h3 
	" About the run
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"Please watch the run first.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Abilities were upgraded so that the wheel could bounce for example. I used the wheel as some kind of my main transport ability when I noticed that nearly all the rooms in the game were flat. The missile was only used if it was faster (like in the water area) or if I needed a grey block-breaking ability.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"The run took me about 3 months in total and several reattempts. The most annoying part was the Dark Mind matches. Especially the 4th Dark Mind is hard to luckmanipulate. 
	$LF
	"I was unable to copy the last match from my 
	[a class=extlink href=http://youtube.com/watch?v=KawYf6U72zQ rel=nofollow 
		"Boss Endurance TAS
	]a
	" so that I was slower maybe. Or Dark Mind just acted different and there's no (big) difference in time.
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		" abuses programming errors in the game
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Aims for fastest time 
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Takes damage to save time 
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Manipulates luck 
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Used emulator: 
		[a class=intlink href=/Forum/T/2050 
			"Visual Boy Advance 1.7.2 rerecording v19.3
		]a
		" 
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h4 
	" UPDATE
	$LF
]h4
[p 
	"The minigame that isn't necessary to be played to finish the game was requested to be played. So the movie file was replaced and the movie time grew from 25:19.8 to 26:11.52
	$LF
]p
[h3 
	" Why Japanese ROM?
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"The Japanese version of the game was used since attacks were more effective.
	$LF
	[del 
		" And a breakable wall which was on the way to Area 4: Moustard Mountain in USA and European version isn't there yet.
	]del
	$LF
]p
[h3 
	" Route
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	"(Note: The name of the area Kirby is in can be read from the screen)
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"For the route please watch the run. Because you have to go through different areas in order to get to a boss, it's quite complicated to explain.
	$LF
	"But I'll list what all pressed switches do:
	$LF
]p
